<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5>give someone one’s word • give someone the word</xh5><p> <i>give someone one’s word—</i>1. give one’s promise to a person: I’ll help you in any way I can—I <u>give you my word</u>. 2. express one’s assurance to a person: I <u>give you my word</u> that my brother did not leave a shilling to his son.</p><p> <i>give someone the word—</i>1. indicate one’s intentions to smb.: Any time you need any additional help just <u>give us the word</u>. 2. command a person to do smth.: The man stood bolt upright before me until I <u>gave him the word</u> to stand at ease. 3. <i>= give someone one’s word 2:</i> I <u>give you the word</u> of a man whose word once meant something—I am playing square with you now.</p> </entry>
